title.5: Peter Parker, the Spectacular Spider-Man Annual (1979) #12
title.7: Silver Sable and the Wild Pack (1992) #1

description.0: The final battle between the Fantastic Four and Occulus the Unforgiving! But what price will they pay for victory and a safe journey home?
description.1: The Cyburai have marked Bobby Drake's family for death!
description.2: Wolverine and Gambit head to Japan to bail out Jubilee, only to be met by a group of deadly ninja assassins known as The Hand!
description.3: The Green Goblin has a strange family dinner at Norman Osborn's old townhouse.
description.10: Spider-Man/Venom team-up! Yes, you've read correctly- Spidey and Venom have a temporary team-up to save J. Jonah Jameson from Carnage. But once Carnage is neutralized, will Venom continue his terrorizing ways?
description.11: The Vision struggles to regain his former humanity as Black Knight comes to admit his growing feelings for Crystal.
description.12: The pressure of being the leader of the Avengers is finally getting to Steve Rogers! Find out the fate of the Avengers when Captain America has finally had enough!
description.13: Moon Knight finds himself without allies and without a home base.  Meet a grittier, darker Moon Knight!  And he'll need that grit as he comes face to face with Doctor Doom!
description.18: What if Thor was a thrall of Set? The Time-Keepers turn their universe-erasing schemes to a world where Thor is wielded like a hammer against the enemies of Set!
description.19: OPERATION: GALACTIC STORM AFTERMATH The dust is still settling after full-on war between the Kree and Shi'ar. In the aftermath to Galactic Storm, Quasar makes the difficult decision to leave the Avengers. Will Wendell Vaughn find his place in the universe by becoming its protector? Kayla Ballantine is still reeling from her encounter with the Angler, and a quantum-leaping adventure with Quasar may be just what the doctor ordered.
description.24: Is the Kingpin set to topple London? The Punisher runs afoul of Interpol while attempting to fulfill a hit.
description.25: She-Hulk's car is mysteriously pulled into outer space, knocking Jen and Weezi out!
description.35: Daredevil works a night shift when he saves New York City’s citizens for 36 hours straight.
description.36: Excalibur clashes in battle with the sinister Necrom, and though they achieve victory, is the cost too high? Which team member won't walk away from the battle? And with the base destroyed, where will Excalibur go?
description.37: Igor Drenkov reveals his original plan to kill Bruce Banner with the G-Bomb test!
description.39: Going undercover is tough work. Can the Punisher romance his way closer to his targets?
description.40: Titania's crime spree continues! Spider-Man steps in when he spots Thor II with the Absorbing Man!
description.42: X-Factor faces off with the Mutant Liberation Front at a clinic in D.C. after a doctor claims to be able to remove the mutant X-gene at birth. Are the doctor's claims true? And will X-Factor be able to maintain peace in the wake of not-so-friendly protest?
description.44: With Franklin still in the captivity of Occulus, time is running out for the Fantastic Four! What dark plot does Occulus have in store for Frankline and his mysterious powers?
description.45: In order to get Bishop acclimated to the current culture, Storm organizes an X-Men night out on the town in New York City. What could go wrong?!
description.46: Bishop accuses Gambit of being the mutant who will betray the X-Men in the future. Can there be any truth to the time-travelling mutant's claim claim?
description.50: Wyatt Wingfoot and the Thing rush to "save" Jen from Mahkizmo's undying love!
description.51: Needing all the help he can get to take out Carnage, Spider-Man recruits good friend Johnny Storm. But will Venom be a willing ally too? Spidey and the Human Torch go the deserted island where Venom lies in wait. Will Eddie Brock be the key to eliminating Carnage?
description.52: The Final Chapter! Operation Galactic Storm Part 19. The Nega-bomb has exploded and the Kree empire is in rubble. But when the Avengers learn that the Supreme Intelligence was behind the destruction of his own people, the team is split down the middle on whether the Supreme Intelligence needs to be executed for his actions. Will an Avenger carry through and execute the Supreme Intelligence?
description.53: When the Kree Galaxy is in danger of being blown up through the use of the Nega-Bomb, the Avengers have to make hard decision to either save the Kree Galaxy or sacrifice one of their own. Read and find out the shocking result!
description.57: OPERATION: GALACTIC STORM PART 16 After the latest assassination attempt, Empress Lilandra demands the blood of her Kree attackers. Will the Avengers be able to encourage peace in the midst of a Galactic Storm? Ultimus awakes from stasis, acting as messenger to the Supreme Intelligence. Deathweb contemplates life as a villain.
description.58: OPERATION: GALACTIC STORM PART 18 In the penultimate chapter of Galactic Storm, the Shi'ar's Nega-Bomb detonates. Simon Williams watches in horror as the Avengers fail to make peace. With such widespread devastation, will Earth's Mightiest be able to pick up the pieces? A challenging issue that explores the true nature of war.
description.59: What if Wolverine had been Lord Vampire during Inferno? The Time-Keepers continue their cosmic gambit, this time with an eye towards a universe where a vampiric Wolverine rises to power as the Earth falls under the veil of Inferno!
description.60: OPERATION: GALACTIC STORM PART 17 Quasar has the near-impossible task of diverting the explosion of the Nega-Bomb, so that its blasts don't destroy Earth. Binary must make a decision that will determine the fate of millions. The stakes have never been higher, as Operation: Galactic Storm enters its final throes!
description.70: A'war'for the'planet'Calamari'erupts over that planet's surface, already threatened by the massive'World Destroyers. While'Lando'and'Wedge'take on the'Imperial'stormtroopers,'Leia'is tormented by visions of'Luke'being sucked into thedarkness. Meanwhile, it seems that'Han'has run into some "old friends"!
description.77: Doctor Strange needs a hero without fear to defeat the Fear Lords. Who do you think he’ll call on…?
description.78: Mary transforms into Typhoid once more once Logan uncovers the truth behind "The Project!"
description.79: The Owl hits a personal low, and makes the tough choice to walk away from all he’s ever known.
description.80: Widget's new, but is he improved? When his upgraded body causes time warps in the lighthouse, it's hard to think so! And why is Merlyn watching from afar?
description.81: Kaos is strapped to an A-Bomb and only Hulk can save him!
description.82: Iron Man, captive of the Kree! Witness as Iron Man faces judgment from Ronan the Accuser!
description.83: Serial killer Roberts shows his true colors in this murder mystery! Sparks fly between Logan and Mary.
description.84: Punisher's undercover mission starts to bear fruit as he's able to cross off more names on his hitlist! Plus, motorcycle chases and bullets galore!
description.85: OPERATION: GALACTIC STORM PART 14 The Avengers appeal to Empress Lilandra for a ceasefire against the Kree. Will the Shi'ar leader call off the Nega-Bomb set to detonate her enemy's empire? Featuring the Kree Starforce, guns loaded with space-age firearms!
description.87: Despite X-Factor's protest, the Mutant Liberation Front stages a prison break for the captured Nasty Boys. What does the MLF have in store next? Cannonball reconnects with his fellow New Mutant Wolfsbane after he notices her lapse in control.
description.89: Assault on the Inniverse! An interdimensional warlord known as Occulus has abducted Sue and Franklin, and the res of the team will stop at nothing to get them back!
description.90: The X-Men finally catch up to Bishop and if anyone has been hoping for a peaceful conversation, they'll be sorely disappointed!
description.91: Wolverine, Mystique, and Spiral confront Mojo to save not only Jubilee, but the entire universe!
description.99: When Cupid hits Mahkizmo with his infamous arrow, the villain falls madly in love with She-Hulk!

4.text: BIOHAZARD AGENDA PART 1 Deathlok’s grip on humanity becomes even more tenuous when he flies into a berserker rage. Will Michael Collins be able to reign himself in? And who will suffer if he loses all control?

5.text: THE HERO KILLERS PART 2.  There's a mysterious villain looking to put an end to Spidey and the New Warriors and this mystery figure is using new and deadlier Dreadnoughts to take down the heroes.

6.text: THE HERO KILLERS PART 4.  The Sphinx is back and he's looking to use Speedball to make himself more powerful than ever!  Can Spider-Man and the New Warriors stop his mad grab for power?

7.text: The heat is on when Hydra kidnaps Silver Sable’s niece! Silver Sable, Spider-Man and Sandman must take down Hydra’s many heads to save young Anna!

8.text: Ghost Rider has been taken over by the Brood! Can the X-Men stop the Spirit of Vengeance?!

9.text: Nick Fury and Luke Cage team up!

14.text: The Thing and Vance's mother testify at his murder trial, while the Warriors do battle with the Folding Circle at the Temple of the Dragon's Breadth.

15.text: The exciting conclusion to the story of Frank Castle's time as a teenage marine in Vietnam.

20.text: Galactus needs Doctor Strange’s help to uncover a mystery about Eternity’s strange behavior.

22.text: When The Punisher guest-stars, all bets are off! Two street-level crime fighters vs. The Untouchables, Hardcore’s personal taskforce. Will Cage and Castle bring the thunder? Yes, and then some.

23.text: Silver Surfer recruits the Guardians to eliminate…Galactus! It’s the team’s most challenging battle yet, as the Guardians duke it out for the fate of future life. Will the all-powerful Surfer be the savior of alienkind?

24.text: Is the Kingpin set to topple London? The Punisher runs afoul of Interpol while attempting to fulfill a hit.

25.text: She-Hulk's car is mysteriously pulled into outer space, knocking Jen and Weezi out!

29.text: The guest-stars keep on coming as the Webbed Wonder is now also joined by Sleepwalker! Will Spidey and his myriad of allies triumph in the end?

30.text: While prowling the campus grounds, Wolverine notices something amiss. An interdimensional portal emerges at Xavier Institute! Wolverine is joined by fellow X-Man Nightcrawler, as the two thwart an invasion by N’Garai aliens. When robbed of his humanity, will Wolverine once again fall to berserker rage? Plus, Maverick crash lands at the Institute with some shadowy dirt on Weapon X…and it involves none other than Deadpool!

31.text: Thanos built a Death Shrine and the Silver Surfer is on his way to destroy it. However, when the Surfer meets Reptyl Prime, a battle begins!

32.text: With Sam back from the dead, Cable realizes that Cannonball must be the High-Lord of the Externals that he has been searching for. As if this revelation was not hard-hitting enough, it is revealed that there is a mole working from inside of the team!

33.text: When advanced attackers attack Adam, he attempts to strike back but his brain his clouded with memories not his own...

35.text: Daredevil works a night shift when he saves New York City’s citizens for 36 hours straight.

38.text: In the aftermath of the Galactic Storm crisis, Tony Stark lays dying - his nervous system paralyzed beyond repair! As Iron Man despairs, he's yanked into the far future, where a race of aliens considers him to be their god! Can Iron Man find it in himself to save their entire civilization? (Originally published as IRON MAN (1992) #280)

47.text: For the protection of his aunt and all he holds dear, Spider-Man has a fateful battle with Adrian Toomes as the Vulture -- and only one will walk away.

48.text: Cage is hired as a bodyguard for a rapper who’s been a recent victim of racial crime. Luke Cage vs. Hammer, a terrorist group whose prime objective is violence against minorities. Cage unleashes his A-game.

49.text: Norrin Radd makes a startling entrance to deliver very bad news. How different is this Silver Surfer of the far future? Who or what is The Keeper?

50.text: Wyatt Wingfoot and the Thing rush to "save" Jen from Mahkizmo's undying love!

54.text:
In the not-so-distant future, Shatterstar rules over Mojoworld. However, when the Spineless Ones orchestrate a rebellion, Shatterstar/Master Programmer must rely on his teammates from the present to save the day.

Note: this digital comic contains "The Crush" & "Know Your Enemy" stories but does not contain the Shattershot story.

55.text: Break into his Main Factory Complex. But why does Deathlok breaks into Stark Prosthetics too? Michael Collins continues his quest for a human body!

56.text: Nick Fury and the agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. must defend the Helicarrier from complete take-over. It’s a battle for the skies, as all havoc breaks loose on S.H.I.E.L.D.’s flying base! Who are the villains behind this infiltration?

61.text: As the Undying Ones overcome Wolverine, he is compelled to fight Doctor Strange and Clea. Then, Doc and Wolverine travel through a Sa’arpool to destroy the Undying Ones!

62.text: Peter David teams-up with writer Fabian Nicieza to tell three X-Factor stories never before seen! Spiral is hunted by Mojo and Val Cooper, but all the six-armed warrior really wants is some time to herself! Val becomes overwhelmed with government bureaucracy. And Strong Guy helps a young boy fend off schoolyard bullies.

64.text: A slave uprising in the Mojoverse! Arize, the leader of this rebellion, flees to Earth to escape Mojo and his footmen. Can the X-Men find and help Arize before he gets captured?

65.text: Frank Castle can't even go food shopping without stirring up some trouble!

66.text: While Marvel Boy has his day in court, the conflict between Tai, the Warriors and the Folding Circle finally comes to a head.

67.text: Frank Castle gets his first taste of combat!

72.text: The vicious battle with the Sinister Six rages on as Spidey and his allies are put on the defensive.

73.text: Wolverine's memories are being mined for a sinister purpose... Can Psylocke and Beast free the rest of the X-Men before he gives up a secret worth killing for?

74.text: When the Silver Surfer fights his alter ego "dark side", he realizes that there is no way to defeat him because they are two pieces of the same person. He then discovers a way to bind them together and get his powers back!

75.text: The battle rages on between X-Force and The Brotherhood. In the midst of battle, X-Force finds a glimmer of hope that revitalizes the team's morale.

76.text: The fearsome fate of the High Evolutionary!

77.text: Doctor Strange needs a hero without fear to defeat the Fear Lords. Who do you think he’ll call on…?

79.text: The Owl hits a personal low, and makes the tough choice to walk away from all he’s ever known.

92.text: In the arms of the Vulture! Aunt May is terrified for her life when Spidey's winged, elderly foe swoops in for the kill. How is May Parker embroiled in Spidey's latest duel?

94.text: Deathlok the Demolisher is back in town! Deathlok makes a triumphant return to doing what he does best- destroying! Plus, what happens when Deathlok encounters Ghost Rider? Too much violence! Guest-starring the Spirit of Vengeance in “Nightmares of Vengeance”!

95.text: With Thrasher off in Cambodia, the New Warriors agonize over Vance's upcoming criminal trial.

96.text: Beginning of a three-part saga flashing back to Frank Castle's time as a marine in Vietnam!

97.text: Luke Cage takes the stage in his own ongoing series! Cage makes himself the ‘Hero for Hire’ for a Chicago newspaper. Cage busts the crime, while the journalists get a story! A perfect arrangement, until Luke encounters Hardcore, a dangerous mobster with an even more dangerous agenda.

98.text: Starhawk’s motivations revealed. Why has he truly returned to the Guardians? Will Rancor find the mutant she’s been tracking? Guest-starring Silver Surfer of the 31st century!

99.text: When Cupid hits Mahkizmo with his infamous arrow, the villain falls madly in love with She-Hulk!
